    "body": "https://github.com/neovim/lua-client will be mostly redundant after `nvim` itself has\n\n- `$NVIM`\n- `--connect` \n- `--remote`-like features \n- ergonomic Lua layer\n\nThen `nvim` itself could be used as the test-runner. Has at least these advantages:\n\n- âœ… eliminates the https://github.com/neovim/lua-client dependency for running tests\n- âœ… eliminates https://github.com/neovim/lua-client and allows us to focus on Nvim as a client to itself\n- ðŸ¤ test code (`helpers.lua`) can use the Nvim Lua stdlib, which eliminates lots of extra `helpers.lua` util functions.",
